2.00	Since_Otar_Left	Since Otar Left	Since Otar Left (original French title: Depuis qu'Otar est parti...) is a 2003 film by director Julie Bertuccelli, based around three Georgian women living in modern-day Tbilisi. It focuses on the attempts of a mother and daughter, Marina and Ada (Dinara Drukarova), to hide the news of their brother's death from Marina's elderly mother, Eka (Esther Gorintin). The film was widely well-received, and won the coveted Critics' Week Grand Prize at the Cannes Film Festival.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/de/Since_Otar_Left_FilmPoster.jpeg/220px-Since_Otar_Left_FilmPoster.jpeg
